ygData.messageBody:
Well, Froggies of course (Guk), and the nearby we saw in trains: some bad
skellies, some bad minos (were they greater minos?) I am still such a newbie
there I can't make it to the zone when we have to run! Stuff was blue and
up to us at 30 - spiders maybe yellow - certainly blue - sometimes we got 3
and 4 in the pull but preferred to get one or two.

Sylly.
-----Original Message-----
From: Kimes, Dean W. [mailto:Dean_Kimes@...]
Sent: Tuesday, October 05, 1999 3:36 PM
To: 'eqbards@onelist.com'
Subject: RE: [eqbards] A trade skill question for the
gallery.

From: "Kimes, Dean W." <Dean_Kimes@...>

What level are the spideys here? Also what else is nearby?
If they are low
enough I have found Lullaby amazingly useful at nodding 4
baddies while I
smack them one at a time.

-----Original Message-----
From: James Schuldes [mailto:jgs@...]
Sent: Tuesday, October 05, 1999 1:54 PM
To: 'eqbards@onelist.com'
Subject: RE: [eqbards] A trade skill question for the
gallery.


From: James Schuldes <jgs@...>

Go camp the bedroom on the dead side of Guk. Pull the
deadly black widows
and you will be sooooo full of that damn spider silk - it
won't be funny.
You can also pull vampire bats and have stacks and stacks of
bat wings. I
master loot for my party and the sheer number of these
things made me turn
on fast destroy for the first time. You need a party for
this spot and got
to watch for trains.

Sylly
